<i>The Mahua blossoms beckon you.</i>

01:44:24.460 --> 01:44:29.475
<i>The woods are alive with love.</i>

01:44:38.273 --> 01:44:43.151
<i>The woods are alive with love.</i>

01:44:43.756 --> 01:44:48.741
<i>The woods are alive with love.</i>

01:44:49.369 --> 01:44:54.097
<i>The woods are alive with love.</i>

01:44:55.511 --> 01:44:58.715
<i>My beloved does not come.</i>

01:45:02.669 --> 01:45:03.931
Wonderful!

01:45:04.915 --> 01:45:07.055
Did Grandma teach you
that as well?

01:45:07.666 --> 01:45:09.555
I had no one else.

01:45:10.778 --> 01:45:13.063
- What about your mother?
- No...

01:45:14.085 --> 01:45:20.150
She died when I was born.
That's how all my troubles started.

01:45:21.004 --> 01:45:26.829
So when this man forced himself
on me, they said...

01:45:27.218 --> 01:45:31.278
"When you were born
your mother died.

01:45:32.984 --> 01:45:37.331
"Now you are no use for anything else".

01:45:38.013 --> 01:45:39.373
What did you say?

01:45:42.208 --> 01:45:45.081
There was a pond behind the house.

01:45:45.905 --> 01:45:48.844
- Understood what I said?
- Yes, you mean pond.

01:45:50.472 --> 01:45:55.398
I wanted to tie a rock around my neck
and drown in that pond.

01:45:55.423 --> 01:45:56.981
Why didn't you do it?

01:45:57.690 --> 01:46:00.562
Because they locked me up.

01:46:01.059 --> 01:46:04.856
Lord, how they hit me...

01:46:04.961 --> 01:46:08.477
slapped me, kicked me.

01:46:08.581 --> 01:46:11.267
They pulled my hair, dragged me...

01:46:11.368 --> 01:46:13.989
and locked me in a room.

01:46:15.116 --> 01:46:20.041
Seven days I lay there without food.

01:46:20.144 --> 01:46:24.786
Nothing to eat, nothing to drink,
not even a drop.

01:46:25.846 --> 01:46:31.286
For seven days and nights
all I did...

01:46:32.253 --> 01:46:35.736
was sit and think how to die.

01:46:38.545 --> 01:46:41.417
Then one day...

01:46:46.509 --> 01:46:50.386
I noticed a box in the corner
of the room.

01:46:53.504 --> 01:46:58.692
I dragged it to the middle
and stood on it.

01:47:00.644 --> 01:47:05.635
I took off my sari and tied
one end around my neck...

01:47:06.922 --> 01:47:08.617
and the other end to the ceiling beam.

01:47:09.609 --> 01:47:11.249
And then what happened?

01:47:12.688 --> 01:47:15.560
- It all went wrong.
- Why?

01:47:22.810 --> 01:47:25.813
Do you think it's easy
to take your own life?

01:47:26.590 --> 01:47:31.034
To leave everything
and disappear forever?

01:47:32.324 --> 01:47:36.521
The festival of Dusshera
was coming in a month.

01:47:36.968 --> 01:47:41.927
I'd wear my new clothes,
drums would beat.

01:47:42.413 --> 01:47:44.325
There would be a fair...

01:47:44.894 --> 01:47:50.235
stalls, lights, a big wheel
and a show.

01:47:53.030 --> 01:47:57.857
In November,
Spuliya would be getting married.

01:47:58.115 --> 01:48:00.333
There would be wedding music.

01:48:00.430 --> 01:48:03.150
The groom would arrive on his horse.

01:48:05.075 --> 01:48:07.925
To leave all this and go...

01:48:09.143 --> 01:48:11.349
and see nothing?

01:48:12.538 --> 01:48:14.907
And I'm not even...

01:48:15.421 --> 01:48:16.473
What?

01:48:17.660 --> 01:48:22.454
My groom would come one day,
my prince...

01:48:23.810 --> 01:48:26.300
like in grandma's stories.

01:48:29.606 --> 01:48:32.194
And I could not die.

01:48:52.441 --> 01:48:53.466
Tea.

01:49:16.847 --> 01:49:18.605
Are you going out?

01:49:19.147 --> 01:49:22.566
Yes, to the lawyer's.

01:49:24.822 --> 01:49:27.607
It's difficult in the daytime.

01:49:27.632 --> 01:49:31.537
If I were your wife,
wouldn't you look at me in the day?

01:49:33.252 --> 01:49:34.369
My wife?

01:49:35.649 --> 01:49:38.807
If you love me,
why don't we marry?

01:49:41.382 --> 01:49:43.597
What will happen to the company
if we get married?

01:49:45.072 --> 01:49:47.016
We'd have to run away.

01:49:47.859 --> 01:49:52.202
Is this place any good?
Are these people good?

01:49:58.205 --> 01:50:03.159
I have a chance, why let it go?

01:50:05.989 --> 01:50:10.922
Am I to be a taxi driver all my life?

01:50:13.357 --> 01:50:16.229
There's no respect in it.

01:50:19.475 --> 01:50:22.609
Everyone is rude to you...

01:50:22.710 --> 01:50:26.391
swear at you, get angry.

01:50:28.316 --> 01:50:31.188
Haggle over the fare.

01:50:34.194 --> 01:50:41.333
Look at the room I'm given to sleep in.
One side is full of sacks.

01:50:45.085 --> 01:50:47.958
This will change
when I have a company.

01:50:49.730 --> 01:50:52.602
I'll never get another opportunity
like this, Gulabi.

01:50:55.437 --> 01:50:56.902
All right, then.

01:51:04.149 --> 01:51:05.262
Gulabi?

01:51:09.140 --> 01:51:10.932
You will come tonight, won't you?

01:51:19.628 --> 01:51:21.367
Greetings!

01:51:21.502 --> 01:51:23.259
Please sit down.

01:51:23.451 --> 01:51:26.716
Singhji is outside.
Shall I ask him in?

01:51:26.752 --> 01:51:29.047
Yes, of course.

01:51:31.210 --> 01:51:33.700
- Just a minute.
- Sir?

01:51:35.301 --> 01:51:36.718
Just a minute...

01:51:39.083 --> 01:51:43.344
Before he comes in,
have you arranged for...

01:51:43.506 --> 01:51:47.667
You've known me for 14 years.

01:51:47.692 --> 01:51:50.728
Have I ever let you down?

01:51:52.054 --> 01:51:54.631
I'll be away for a few days.

01:51:54.656 --> 01:51:58.559
But you are here tonight, aren't you?

01:51:58.584 --> 01:52:01.784
Don't worry,
I have something special for you.

01:52:10.428 --> 01:52:11.454
This is Singh.

01:52:21.142 --> 01:52:26.232
- I've heard a lot about you. Sit down.
- I'm fine here.

01:52:27.132 --> 01:52:30.452
Fine? There is a chair, please sit down.

01:52:31.344 --> 01:52:36.084
How can we talk if you keep standing?

01:52:36.718 --> 01:52:37.906
Sit down.

01:52:45.916 --> 01:52:51.836
Singhji's family has lived in Bengal
for five generations.

01:52:51.877 --> 01:52:53.806
I see!

01:52:54.311 --> 01:53:00.336
In my grandfather's time a coachman
would not dare sit with us.

01:53:00.361 --> 01:53:03.159
Today we are all equals.

01:53:07.015 --> 01:53:12.048
- The thing is, Mr. Mansingh...
- Narsingh!

01:53:12.814 --> 01:53:15.930
Narsingh? means Narasingha...
That's very good.

01:53:16.946 --> 01:53:21.834
Mr. Narsingh, I don't know you.

01:53:23.448 --> 01:53:27.609
He is a friend, a trusted friend.

01:53:27.996 --> 01:53:32.507
Because of him,
I agreed to talk to you.

01:53:33.795 --> 01:53:38.502
You know all about cars...

01:53:38.600 --> 01:53:40.707
you even have experience.

01:53:41.385 --> 01:53:47.021
You are also wise and clever.
That is your capital.

01:53:47.908 --> 01:53:49.908
- No hard cash...
- Cash?

01:53:52.854 --> 01:53:55.190
You are not investing any money.

01:53:55.516 --> 01:53:58.246
- What about my car?
- Car?

01:53:58.579 --> 01:54:00.272
I'm putting my car into the deal.

01:54:00.373 --> 01:54:03.311
- What car?
- I have only one car, a Chrysler.

01:54:03.914 --> 01:54:06.814
The one outside with the canvas top?
That honks away?

01:54:07.305 --> 01:54:08.638
That... crap?

01:54:09.703 --> 01:54:13.013
You mean my car is no good?
Ask him.

01:54:13.038 --> 01:54:17.260
He doesn't mean it's bad or anything,

01:54:17.601 --> 01:54:21.225
he means that if you have
a new company...

01:54:21.250 --> 01:54:27.564
you can't go about in a taxi
that's 25 years old.

01:54:27.925 --> 01:54:28.951
Exactly.

01:54:29.760 --> 01:54:35.297
You belong to the rising generation.
If you cling to old things...

01:54:35.398 --> 01:54:39.277
- What shall I do with it?
- Sell it.

01:54:39.834 --> 01:54:41.036
Sell it.

01:54:41.260 --> 01:54:44.874
If you get 700 rupees,
put it into the company.

01:54:45.313 --> 01:54:49.278
But your share will be one-third.

01:54:49.352 --> 01:54:55.138
Full partnership is no small
consideration. Well, Singhji?

01:55:05.339 --> 01:55:08.211
Don't you like the offer?

01:55:09.567 --> 01:55:14.558
It's a good car, it's served me well.

01:55:16.005 --> 01:55:18.725
The engine's smooth.

01:55:20.028 --> 01:55:21.138
Singhji...

01:55:26.384 --> 01:55:30.199
Look at this brand new set of teeth.

01:55:30.742 --> 01:55:34.422
I once owned the 1910 model.

01:55:34.966 --> 01:55:39.718
They were no good anymore,
I had them pulled out.

01:55:43.927 --> 01:55:49.017
Now I can eat the toughest meat.

01:55:55.754 --> 01:55:56.760
All right.

01:56:05.306 --> 01:56:06.322
Singhji...

01:56:10.992 --> 01:56:15.292
I see a smile on your face at last.

01:56:17.283 --> 01:56:18.495
Rama?

01:56:21.001 --> 01:56:22.010
Singhji...

01:56:24.595 --> 01:56:28.336
I can get at least 1,000 rupees
for this car.

01:56:28.361 --> 01:56:32.063
That's guaranteed.
Don't worry about the price.

01:56:40.835 --> 01:56:45.274
There's only one thing left now.

01:56:47.075 --> 01:56:48.106
What?

01:56:49.810 --> 01:56:51.183
The ghee tin.

01:56:56.359 --> 01:56:58.157
Start the car.

01:57:09.511 --> 01:57:14.626
Here's the address, drive straight in.
Give it to Mr. Jaggu.

01:57:15.191 --> 01:57:16.306
Okay.

01:57:22.951 --> 01:57:23.951
Singhji...

01:57:29.612 --> 01:57:32.430
Do you want to take this?

01:57:45.639 --> 01:57:46.713
Singhji?

01:57:51.006 --> 01:57:52.715
Will you sell the car?

01:57:53.809 --> 01:57:58.101
Yes. Anything to say about that?

01:57:59.342 --> 01:58:00.627
Give it to me.

01:58:00.735 --> 01:58:04.388
- Why should I give it to you?
- I will drive it.

01:58:05.367 --> 01:58:07.731
Can you pay me 1,000 rupees for it?

01:58:09.836 --> 01:58:14.616
Not now, but in two years,
when I run a taxi service.

01:58:15.442 --> 01:58:19.558
What service? Won't you stay with me,
in my company?

01:58:21.357 --> 01:58:26.259
How can I stay without a car?
I can't do it.

01:58:28.492 --> 01:58:32.301
Bastard! Don't let me see
your face again!

01:59:09.611 --> 01:59:13.543
- I know.
- So why are you here?

01:59:15.750 --> 01:59:20.033
You will take that and deliver it.

01:59:21.355 --> 01:59:22.718
I know.

01:59:24.486 --> 01:59:28.048
Sukhanram's friends, such gentlemen.

01:59:31.098 --> 01:59:32.787
What is it to you?

01:59:36.575 --> 01:59:40.935
I know what's inside. Opium.

01:59:42.341 --> 01:59:43.870
Isn't that a sin?

01:59:45.526 --> 01:59:48.593
My wife ran away. Wasn't that a sin?

01:59:52.304 --> 01:59:54.248
You come to my room at night.

01:59:56.165 --> 01:59:57.541
Isn't that a sin?

02:00:00.298 --> 02:00:06.250
Yes, it is. For a girl like me,
to love is a sin.

02:00:13.878 --> 02:00:19.586
I'll be back in an hour. Come then.

02:00:21.362 --> 02:00:22.508
Why?

02:00:24.703 --> 02:00:26.427
Why should I come?

02:00:28.323 --> 02:00:32.451
I'm asking you to come.
Won't you come?

02:00:34.388 --> 02:00:37.670
Are you my boss, to be obeyed?

02:00:38.988 --> 02:00:39.989
Gulabi?

02:00:40.835 --> 02:00:46.787
Don't you know who my boss is?
He's your boss, too.

02:00:48.502 --> 02:00:50.744
Salaam, Rana Pratap Singh.

02:00:52.350 --> 02:00:53.376
Gulabi...

02:01:51.334 --> 02:01:54.806
- Listen, I have important news.
- What is that?

02:01:55.320 --> 02:01:57.329
Sukhanram's house
is going to be raided.

02:01:57.596 --> 02:01:59.847
I overheard the boss.

02:02:00.125 --> 02:02:04.155
I thought I'd warn you to watch out.

02:02:04.258 --> 02:02:08.670
I'll be back in an hour, see you then.

02:02:08.774 --> 02:02:12.762
- Where are you off to?
- Work, a few repairs.

02:02:12.787 --> 02:02:14.906
All right, I'm going home.

02:02:44.545 --> 02:02:46.572
I'll help you start up.

02:03:23.079 --> 02:03:24.262
Joseph...

02:03:33.710 --> 02:03:35.825
Where are you going?

02:04:15.202 --> 02:04:19.026
Well done. Warrior.

02:04:29.245 --> 02:04:30.291
Joseph...

02:04:55.154 --> 02:04:57.337
Joseph...

02:05:00.370 --> 02:05:05.361
I'll be back, Joseph.

02:05:46.327 --> 02:05:47.597
Mr Sukhanram.

02:05:53.579 --> 02:05:54.728
Mr Sukhanram?

02:06:06.290 --> 02:06:08.234
- He's gone out.
- Where?

02:06:08.623 --> 02:06:10.098
To the lawyer's.

02:06:20.358 --> 02:06:21.823
Has the boss gone out?

02:06:22.113 --> 02:06:23.295
Yes, Singhji.

02:06:23.422 --> 02:06:24.765
Was anyone with him?

02:06:25.781 --> 02:06:27.105
That girl.
(Gulabi)

02:06:36.870 --> 02:06:38.731
- Come on.
- Where to?

02:06:38.756 --> 02:06:40.962
We've work to do.

02:07:12.476 --> 02:07:16.358
Gulabi, come with me.

02:07:21.067 --> 02:07:23.655
The game's up. Taxi service is over.

02:07:33.063 --> 02:07:37.436
- Where are we going?
- Home, Gulabi.

02:07:42.159 --> 02:07:46.349
Thieves! Stop them!

02:08:01.753 --> 02:08:02.998
I'm going, Joseph.

02:08:08.816 --> 02:08:11.175
I'm off to Giribraja!
See you there.

02:08:38.601 --> 02:08:40.518
THE END